SIMPLE: muggins
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Muggins
<hw>Mug"gins</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Etym.
unknown.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A game of dominoes in which the object
is to make the sum of the two ends of the line some multiple of
five.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A game at cards which depends upon building in suits
or matching exposed cards, the object being to get rid of one's
cards.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Muggins</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Muggins
<hw>Mug"gins</hw>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <def>In certain games, to score
against, or take an advantage over (an opponent), as for an error,
announcing the act by saying ⟦ldquo⟧muggins.⟦rdquo⟧</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Muggish</ent>⟦br⟧
